# Frontend Testing Standards

This document defines testing requirements and patterns for web application components, pages, and user flows.

---

## Testing Pyramid

| Level | Tool | Speed | Scope | When to Use |
|-------|------|-------|-------|-------------|
| Unit | Vitest / Jest | Fast | Single function/component | Pure logic, utilities, hooks |
| Component | Testing Library | Fast | Single component in isolation | Rendering, props, events |
| Integration | Testing Library | Medium | Multiple components together | User flows within a page |
| E2E | Playwright / Cypress | Slow | Full application | Critical user journeys |
| Visual | Chromatic / Percy | Medium | Screenshot comparison | Layout, styling changes |
| Accessibility | axe-core | Fast | WCAG compliance | All components |

---

## Component Testing

### What to Test

- [ ] Component renders without crashing (smoke test)
- [ ] Props affect rendered output correctly
- [ ] User interactions trigger expected callbacks
- [ ] Loading, error, and empty states render correctly
- [ ] Accessibility: keyboard navigation and ARIA attributes
- [ ] Edge cases: very long text, missing data, boundary values

### What NOT to Test

- Implementation details (internal state, method calls)
- CSS styling (use visual regression instead)
- Third-party library internals

### Testing Library Patterns

```typescript
import { render, screen, fireEvent } from '@testing-library/react';

describe('SearchInput', () => {
  it('calls onSearch when user types and submits', async () => {
    const onSearch = vi.fn();
    render(<SearchInput onSearch={onSearch} />);

    const input = screen.getByRole('searchbox');
    await fireEvent.change(input, { target: { value: 'query' } });
    await fireEvent.submit(input.closest('form')!);

    expect(onSearch).toHaveBeenCalledWith('query');
  });

  it('shows loading indicator during search', () => {
    render(<SearchInput isLoading={true} />);
    expect(screen.getByRole('status')).toHaveTextContent(/loading/i);
  });

  it('displays error message on failure', () => {
    render(<SearchInput error="Network error" />);
    expect(screen.getByRole('alert')).toHaveTextContent('Network error');
  });
});
```

### Query Priority (Testing Library)

Use queries in this order of preference:

1. `getByRole` -- accessible role queries (preferred)
2. `getByLabelText` -- form elements
3. `getByPlaceholderText` -- when label is not available
4. `getByText` -- non-interactive content
5. `getByTestId` -- last resort

