## E2E Testing

### Critical User Journeys (MUST have E2E tests)

- [ ] User registration and login
- [ ] Core feature happy path
- [ ] Payment/checkout flow (if applicable)
- [ ] Error recovery (network failure, invalid input)
- [ ] Cross-browser compatibility (Chrome, Firefox, Safari)

### Playwright Patterns

```typescript
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';

test('user can create and save a document', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('/');
  await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'New Document' }).click();
  await page.getByRole('textbox', { name: 'Title' }).fill('My Document');
  await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Save' }).click();

  await expect(page.getByText('Document saved')).toBeVisible();
});
```

